Dozens of gleaming giant white sculptures are rising from a desolate and frozen corner of China in preparation for an amazing annual snow sculpture festival.

Hundreds of workmen are hacking away at thousands of tonnes of snow to create the stunning works of art - some measuring more than 26 metres tall and 117 metres wide - for the annual Harbin 
International Snow Sculpture Art Expo.

Each January the capital city of the Heilongjiang Province hosts a magnificent winter festival is held on the Chinese and Russian border.

