This year marks the 29th, and could be one of the most amazing yet.

Staff were today putting in late preparations for the Sun Island International Snow Sculpture Art Expo.

A series of photographs have captured the army of skilled workmen perching on frozen ledges and using shovels and picks to add the fine details to the works.

